==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lenticel
<hw>Len"ti*cel</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧n"t⟦icr⟧*s⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>lenticelle</ets>, dim. fr. L. <ets>lens</ets>,
<ets>lentis</ets>, a lentil. Cf. <er>Lentil</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of the small, oval, rounded
spots upon the stem or branch of a plant, from which the underlying
tissues may protrude or roots may issue, either in the air, or more
commonly when the stem or branch is covered with water or earth.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A small, lens-shaped gland on the under side of some
leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lenticellate</ent>⟦br⟧
